  "summary": "Main\nBy Daniel Hynes\nRising geopolitical risks triggered a rerating of the risk premium in energy markets. However, lacklustre demand in China weighed on sentiment elsewhere. Crude oil prices were under pressure early in the session after reports suggest Israel was delaying its ground invasion as the US readied air defence to protect American troops in the region.",
